<para>
  Change the default <xref linkend="Enum-CacheType"/> used to store time step
  data for new &meshes;.  If <varname>cachetype</varname> is
  <userinput>Memory</userinput>, the data will be stored in RAM.  If
  it's <userinput>Disk</userinput>, the data will be stored in
  temporary files on disk.  Storage in RAM is usually faster, but more
  data can usually be stored on disk.
</para>
<para>
  This command only affects new &meshes;.  To change the cache type
  for an existing &mesh;, use <xref
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Modify"/> with
  <varname>modifier</varname>=<xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-SetMeshDataCacheType"/>.
</para>
<para>
  In the GUI, this command is invoked from the
  <guimenuitem>Settings</guimenuitem> menu in the main &oof2; window's
  menubar.
</para>


